cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with facial landmark localization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using texture and pose information to initialize the landmark localization, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on a dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of multitask cascaded convolutional networks suggests the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
